  "name": "Bursting Bloom",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You cause a rose bush to sprout from the chest of a foe, bursting out of its body and wrapping it in thorned vines. The target takes @Damage[6d6[piercing]] damage and @Damage[1d6[persistent,bleed]] damage and must attempt a Fortitude save. When the target is no longer taking persistent bleed damage and is no longer encumbered, the rose bush withers away to nothing.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage and no persistent damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and persistent damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.D5mg6Tc7Jzrj6ro7]{Encumbered} for 4 rounds.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage and persistent damage and is encumbered for 1 minute.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+2)</strong> The initial damage increases by 3d6, and the persistent bleed damage increases by [[/r 1d6]].</p>"
    },
